name: description
latin_name: The latin name of the test species.
effect: The effect that was being tested.
lifestage: The lifestage the species was during the test.
effect_conc_mg.L: Contaminant concentration that corresponds to the endpoint
effect_conc_std_mg.L: The effect concentration standardized to include the acute to chronic ratio to extrapolate acute and/or effect concentrations to chronic and/or no-effect concentrations in mg/L.
ecological_group: Identification of salmonids and planktonic invertebrates. If neither of these, listed as “other”.
species_present_in_bc: Species is present in British Columbia if entry = TRUE.
